<body>
    <h1>Contract Guidelines</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-APIInformation">API Information</h3>
<p>Basic information help others understand what functionality your API has=
. This information&nbsp;is displayed in Westpac Mesh Connect, so it is impo=
rtant in helping consumers discover your API.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"417" src=3D"f04b68a6ca0508fba234170209728982e032fb166f730b108b6c04a3d4=
415608" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
8-33-3.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571075013&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279312" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_8-33-3.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Version: The version of your API. This follows <a href=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/mesh/Versioning" rel=3D"nofollow">semantic=
 versioning</a>, and must be updated whenever changes are made to the API.<=
/li>
<li>Title: The display name of your API. This is typically determined durin=
g naming governance, and should closely match your API's shortname. eg. An =
API with name 'cap-technolsvcdsgndvlpmt-applnmgt-<em>meshcmpntmgt</em>-v1' =
should have 'Mesh Component Management' as the title.</li>
<li>Description: A high level business description of what your API does.</=
li>
<li>X-goldenVersion: The version number of the golden template your API is =
based on. When possible, this should always be kept in sync with the latest=
 Golden Template.</li>
<li>Host/basepath/schemes: These values should already be auto-generated, a=
nd should not be modified.</li>
<li>SecurityDefinitions: For non-proxy APIs, this should not be modified. A=
PIs on the internal gateway will communicate with basic authorisation.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>
<p>Your swagger will come with predefined mandatory headers that are used i=
nternally by Westpac Mesh. You typically should not modify these parameters=
, but feel free to add your own query/path parameters as required.&nbsp;</p=
>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> If using OpenAPI, these headers are automatically=
 injected for you at runtime, and you do not need to manually declare them.=
</p>
<p><strong><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embed=
ded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"fals=
e" height=3D"345" src=3D"25a6ff5063c4f0b362ef83139f0edc8ccbdb53f0589e0d4385=
f3721a4d5b28c5" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image202=
1-11-30_8-54-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074963&amp;ap=
i=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203=
279311" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"att=
achment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_8-54-39.png"=
 data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resour=
ce-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"12032793=
07" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></s=
pan></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>X-messageId: A GUID to represent a single transaction between a single =
component and another component on the platform. When implementing your API=
, this value should NOT be propogated.</li>
<li>X-appCorrelationId: A GUID to represent an end-to-end transaction, acro=
ss multiple components. This value should be propagated, Westpac Mesh provi=
ders <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/=
lib-westpac-digital-platform-wdp-helpers/browse" class=3D"external-link" re=
l=3D"nofollow">helper libraries</a> to assist with implementation.</li>
<li>X-organisationId: The organisation the caller is operating in. Note thi=
s is not the same as brand.</li>
<li>X-originatingSystemId: The Alfabet Id of the calling application</li>
<li>X-consumerType: The originating consumption channel invoking the API.</=
li>
<li>X-userId/X-userIdScheme: These should be used to identify the user invo=
king the API if required.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Paths</strong></p>
<p>Here you can define your resources/endpoints required by your API. Note =
that the GET /healthcheck is mandatory and should not be modified.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"367" src=3D"1cde2d6e251b1b25d9062ec7cb6f2a9c0981f9b5ff5932b8d6252fa36e=
95996c" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
9-14-58.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074910&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279310" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_9-14-58.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Tags: This will appear as a title for your endpoint when viewed in the =
Swagger Editor.</li>
<li>OperationId: This will determine the name of the related classes when y=
ou generate code from your swagger.</li>
<li>Parameters: Mandatory headers will already be defined here. Feel free t=
o additional parameters more as required.</li>
<li>Responses: Here you can reference any defined response objects for each=
 HTTP error code.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-Responses">Responses</h3>
<p>Here you can define your response objects. Please note that HTTP 200 res=
ponses should ALWAYS have a 'data' object at the root level, which wraps yo=
ur response entity. At the root level, you may also have a 'paging' object.=
</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"242" src=3D"a6e4dc974e14972975ad370abccdbf04eddc0e8622f2c137599d44c3ee=
c0962a" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
9-27-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074720&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279308" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_9-27-39.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>HTTP 400 and 500 error responses should list out all possible error code=
s and messages in their description. A table format should be used for ease=
 of reading.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"140" src=3D"d7d1c96aa5c57364f6b103f05e672203f628055b2a579d2e80c3854a81=
bcf68e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
9-24-27.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074803&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279309" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_9-24-27.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-Definitions">Definitions</h3>
<p>Here you can define your response objects. You should write object defin=
itions with the intent of reuse across your swagger. Some other points to c=
onsider:</p>
<ul>
<li>Always include examples where possible. Ideally, examples should be at =
the field level, rather than the object level.</li>
<li>Pay attention to the naming of your definitions, as these your generate=
d classed will have the same names code is generating from the swagger.</li=
>
<li>Enums should not contain spaces, and have consistent casing</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-FurtherExamples">Further Examples</h3>
<p>You can find more examples in the <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westp=
ac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/examples" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">Contracts repository</a> and in <a href=3D"https://m=
esh.westpac.com.au/components/apis" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">Mesh Connect</a>, by searching for 'Reference Implementation'.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Sample OpenAPI contracts:</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/reference-scoped-=
access-v1?tab=3Dcontract" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://=
mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/reference-scoped-access-v1?tab=3Dcontra=
ct</a></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/mesh-component-qu=
ality-metrics-v2?tab=3Dcontract" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">h=
ttps://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/mesh-component-quality-metrics-v=
2?tab=3Dcontract</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Sample Swagger contracts:</p>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/component=
s/apis/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-meshcmpnt-v1?tab=3Dcontract" rel=3D"=
nofollow">https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-lo=
gclitcmpnt-meshcmpnt-v1?tab=3Dcontract</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
